    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay, i get the theory part. but if the meaning of words has changed so much over 200 years, doesn't originalism basically just freeze the country in the past and prevent us from protecting rights that the founders couldn't have even imagined? like, isn't a \"living constitution\" approach more logical for a modern society?",
